dct_description_sm: C.P. Patterson, superintendent ; verified J.E. Hilgard, assist. in charge of office and topography ; triangulation and topography by L.A. Sengteller, assist., in 1876 ; hydrography by Comdr. G.W. Coffin, U.S.N., assist., in 1879.
Relief shown by hachures; depths by soundings.
Notes on tides, soundings, and Fort Ross Cove general information.
Shows low water areas, small islands, buildings, roads, drainage.
Old sheet number 694 crossed out. "5651" stamped on.
